quotes.quote: Captain.
Tell them we wish to board at once.
I don't sense anything.
Don't center on your anxiety, Obi-Wan. Keep your concentration here and now where it belongs.
.....but not at the expense of the moment. Be mindful of the living Force, my young Padawan.
These Federation types are cowards. The negotiations will be short.
Destroyer droids!
It's a standoff! Let's go!
Battle droids.
It's an odd play for the Trade Federation. We've got to warn the Naboo and contact Chancellor Valorum. Let's split up. Stow aboard separate ships and meet down on the planet.
Let go!
Are you brainless? You almost got us killed!
The ability to speak does not make you intelligent. Now get outta here!
That wont be necessary.
I have no time for this now...
Stay down!
You forgot to turn your power off again, didn't you?
It won't take long to recharge, but this is a lesson I hope you've learned, my young Padawan.
A local. Let's go, before more of those droids show up.
A city! Can you take us there?
No??!
You hear that?
That's the sound of a thousand terrible things heading this way...
Much farther?
That droid army is about to attack the Naboo. We must warn them.
Then speed us on our way.
We need a transport.
Thank you for your help. We go in peace.
A transport, I hope.
Thank you, my friend.
We'll need a navigator to get us through the planet's core. This Gungan my be of help.
What is to become of Jar Jar Binks here?
He has been a great help to us. I hope the punishment will not be too severe.
We need a navigator to get us through the planet's core. I have saved Jar Jar Binks' life. He owes me what you call a life debt.
Your gods demand that his life belongs to me now.
You're the navigator.
Just relax, the Force will guide us...
Full speed ahead.
There's always a bigger fish.
Stay calm. We're not in trouble yet.
Relax.
Head for that outcropping.
Get this thing started.
Come on...
Come on, Jar Jar.
Your Highness, we are the Ambassadors, for the Supreme Chancellor.
The negotiations never took place. Your Highness, we must make contact with the republic.
Do you have transports?
That won't be a problem. Your Highness, under the circumstances, Isuggest you come to Coruscant with us.
They will kill you if you stay.
The situation here is not what it seems. There is something else behind all this, Your Highness. There is no logic in the Federation's move here. My feelings tell me they will destroy you.
If you are to leave, Your Highness, it must be now.
I'm Ambassador for the Supreme Chancellor, and I'm taking those people to Coruscant.
We'll have to land somewhere to refuel and repair the ship.
It's controlled by the Hutts...
...It would be no different than if we landed on a system controlled by the Federation...except the Hutts aren't looking for her, which gives us an advantage.

Yor Highness, we are heading for a remote planet called Tatooine. It is a system far beyond the reach of the Trade Federation. There we will be able to make needed repairs, then travel on to Coruscant.
You must trust my judgement, Your Highness.
Land near the outskirts. We don't want to attract any attention.
Don't let them send ant transmissions. Be wary...I sense a disturbance in the Force.
No more commands from Her Highness today, Captain. This spaceport is not going to be pleasant...
I don't have time to argue. But this is not a good idea. Stay close to me.
...moisture farms for the most part, but also a few indigenous tribes and scavengers. The few spaceports like this one are havens for those who do not wish to be found...
We'll try one of the smaller dealers.
I need parts for a J-type 327 Nubian.
My droid here has a readout of what I need.
Don't touch anything.
I have 20,000 Republic dataries.
I don't have anything else. But credits will do fine.
Credits will do fine.
...Obi-Wan, you're sure there isn't anything of value left on board?
All right. Another solution will present itself. I'll check back.
Not likely. We have nothing of value, that's our problem.
Nevertheless, the boy is right...you were heading for trouble. Thank you, my young friend.
We'll hed back to our ship.
I'm Qui-Gon Jinn, and this is Jar Jar Binks.
Your son was kind enough to offer us shelter.
I have enough food for a meal.
He's a very special boy.
It sounds like bait to establish a connection trace.
Either way, we're running out of time.
They have Podracing on Malastare. Very fast, very dangerous.
You must have Jedi reflexes if you race Pods.
Don't do that again.
What?
What makes you think that?
Perhaps I killed a Jedi and stole it from him.
I wish that were so...
No, I'm afraid not...
I can see there's no fooling you... You mustn't let anyone know about us...we're on our way to Coruscant, the central system in the Republic, on a very important mission, and it must be kept secret.
I believe you can, but our first job is to aquire the parts we need...
Podracing... Greed can be a powerful ally.. if it's used properly.
Your mother's right. Is there anyone friendly to the Republic who might be able to help us?
The Queen does not need to know.
My ship will be the entry fee.
It's in good order, except for the parts we need.
I have...acquired a Pod in a game of chance. "The fastest ever built."
Fifty-fifty!?! If it's going to be fifty-fifty, I suggest you front the cash for the entry. If we win, you keep all the winnings, minus the cost of the parts I need...If we lose, you keep my ship.
Either way, you win.
A ship without a power supply will not get us anywhere, and there is something about this boy...
You should be proud of your son. He gives without any thought of reward.
He has special powers.
He can see things before they happen. That's why he appears to have such quick reflexes. It is a Jedi trait.
The Force is unusally strong with him, that much is clear. Who was his father?
I'm afraid not. Had he been born in the Republic, we would have identified him early, and he would have become Jedi, no doubt...he has the way. But it's too late for him now, he's too old.
I think it's time we found out. Use this power charge.
Sit still, Annie. Let me clean this cut.
Most of them.
Not likely.
There, good as new...
Checking your blood for infections.
Go on, you have a big day tomorrow. Goodnight.
Obi-Wan...
Make an analysis of this blood sample I'm sending you.
I need a midi-chlorian count.
What are your readings?
Here's a signal check.
That's it then.
No Jedi has.
I'm not sure.
Patience, my blue friend. You'll have your winnings before the suns set, and we'll be far away from here.
You don't think Anakin will win?
Why?
I'll take that bet.
I'll wager my new racing pod against...say...the boy and his mother.
The boy is small, he can't be worth much.
For the fastest Pod ever built?!
Both, or no bet.
The boy, then...
I'll tell you later.
Of course you will.
Are you all set, Annie? May the Force be with you.
He's fine.
The Queen trusts my judgment, young handmaiden. You should too.
Yes, sir?
Yes, sir.
With all due respect for the Trade Federation, the Ambassodors for the Supreme Chancellor wish to board immediately.
Yes, yes, of coarse...ahhh...as you know, our blockade is perfectly legal, and we'd be happy to receive the Ambassador...Happy to.
What?!? What did you say?
They must be dead by now. Blast, what's left of them.
What in blazes is going on down there?
Well, not exactly, but I don't... Seal off the bridge.
I want destroyer droids up here at once!!!
Close the blast doors!!!
Impossible!! This is impossible!!
At last we're getting results.
Again you come before me, Your highness. The Federation is pleased.
I was not aware of such a failure.
I take it you know the outcome. I wonder why they bother to vote.
I know nothing about any Ambassadors...you must be mistaken.
Your Highness, we would never do anything without the approval of the Senate. You assume too much.
It's too late now.
I don't know, but we must move quickly to disrupt all communications down there.
Excellent.
The invasion is on schedule, My Lord.
The Queen has great faith the Senate will side with her.
Thank you, My Lord.
No need to report that to him, until we have something to report.
Ah, victory!
The Naboo and the Federation will forge a treaty that will legitimize our occupation here. I've been assured it will be ratified by the Senate.
Now, now, your Highness. You are not going to like what we have in store for your people. In time, their suffering will persuade you to see our point of view. Commander. Process them.
We control all the cities in the North and are searching for any other settlements...
She has disappeared, My Lord. One Naboo cruiser got pat the blockade.
My Lord, it's impossible to locate the ship. It's out of our range.
Yes, My Lord. The hologram fades off.
This is getting out of hand...now there are two of them.
I have a bad feeling about this.
It's not about the mission, Master, it's something...elsewhere...elusive.
Master Yoda says I should be mindful of the future...
Yes, Master...how do you think the trade viceroy will deal with the chancellor's demands?
Offhand, I'd say this mission is past the negotiation stage.
They have shield generators!
It's an invisible army.
You were right about one thing, Master. The negotiations were short.
Sorry, Master, the water fried my weapon.
Yes, Master.
What's this?
When they find us, they will crush us, grind us into little pieces, then blast us into oblivion!
Don't worry, this has not been our day for warm welcomes.
After those droids take control of the surface, they will come here and take control of you.
You and the Naboo form a symbiont circle. What happens to noe of you will affect the other. You must understand this.
Master, whats a bongo?
We are short of time, Master.
Master, why do you keep dragging these pathetic life forms along with us?...Here, take over.
Why were you banished, Jar Jar?
They banished you because you're clumsy?
Give me the controls.
.....we're losing power.
Power's back.
You overdid it.
What is it?
Get up here!
That was close.
I'll take care of that.
Now stay here, and keep out of trouble.
Here, Master. Tatooine... It's small, out of the way, poor... The Trade Federation has no presence there.
It's risky...but there's no alternative.
That's it. Tatooine.
Sorry, Qui-Gon's right. You'll make things less obvious.
The Hyperdrive generator is gone. We will need a new one.
I fell it also, Master.
A few containers of supplies, the Queen's wardrobe, maybe. Not enough for you to barter with. Not in the amounts you're talking about.
This storm's going to slow them down.
It's a trick. Send no reply... Send no transmission of any kind.
...the Queen is upset...but absolutely no reply was sent.
What if it is true and the people are dying?
What if this plan fails, Master? We could be stuck here for a long time.
Yes, Master.
Wait a minute...
All right. I've got it.
Something must be wrong with the transmission.
Strange. The transmission seems to be in good order, but the reading's off the chart...over twenty thousand.
Even Master Yoda doesn't have a midi-chlorian count that high!
What does it mean?
I knew it! They were sent to force a settlement, eh. Blind me, we're done for!
Have you ever encountered a Jedi Knight before, sir?
That won't be enough, sir.
We will not survive this.
...They're still coming through!
Where are those destroyer droids?!
We have them on the run, sir...they're no match for destroyer droids.
It's Queen Amidala herself.
She's right, the Senate will never....
Do you think she suspects an attack?
...and there is no trace of the Jedi. They may have gotton onto one of your landing craft.
You didn't tell him about the missing Jedi?
We should not have made this bargain. What will happen when the Jedi become aware of these Sith Lords?
Sir, they've gone up the ventilation shaft.
Sir, a transmission from the planet.
You will not be pleased when you hear what I have to say, Viceroy...Your trade boycott of our planet has ended.
I have word that the Senate is finally voting on this blockade of yours.
Enough of this pretense, Viceroy! I'm aware the Chancellor's Ambassadors are with you now, and that you have been commanded to reach a settlement.
Beware, Viceroy....the Federation is going too far this time.
We will see.
Senator Palpatine?!? What's happening?
Don't jump to conclusions, Governor. The Federation would not dare go that far.
We must continue to rely on negotiation.
I will not condone a course of action that will lead us to war.
I will not co-operate.
Thank you, Ambassador, but my place is here with my people.
Either choice presents a great risk...to all of us...
We are brave, Your Highness.
Then, I will plead our case before the Senate. Be careful, Governor.
It is to be commended...what is its number?
Thank you, Artoo Detoo. You have proven to be very loyal...Padme!
Continue, Captain.
That's all right.
Thank you. This little guy is quite a mess.
I'm Padme, I attend Her Highness, You're a Gungan, aren't you? How did you end up here with us?
I've been trained in defense... I can take care of myself.
....like us.
What?
I've never heard of angels.
You're a funny little boy. How do you know so much?
You're...a slave?
I'm sorry. I don't fully understand. This is a strange world to me.
I'm glad I met you,....ah...
Anakin.
Padme Naberrie.
And that works for you.
On the outskirts.
...and our droid, Artoo-Detoo.
He's wonderful!
He's perfect.
I can't believe there is still slavery in the galaxy. The Republic's anti-slavery laws...
Our ship was damaged, and we're stranded here until we can repair it.
These junk dealers must have a weakness of some kind.
I'm sure Qui-Gon doesn't want to put your son in danger. We will find another way...
Are you sure about this? Trusting our fate to a boy we hardly know. The Queen will not approve.
Well, I don't approve.
I hope you're about finished.
I hope not; I hate fighting. Your mother wants you to come in and clean up. We have to leave soon.
He and Jar Jar left already. They're with Watto at the arena.
Do what?
You've never won a race?
Not even finished?!
You carry all our hopes.
You Jedi are far too reckless. The Queen...
You assume too much.
Here he comes!
...How could that be true? I have assurances from the Chancellor...his Ambassadors did arrive. It must be the...get...negotiate...
Check the transmission generators...
It could be the Federation jamming us. Your Highness.
The Senate would revoke their trade franchise, and they'd be finished.
This is a dangerous situation, Your Highness. Our security volunteers will be no match against a battle-hardened Federation army.
They've knocked out all our communications.
In the main hanger. This way.
There are too many of them.
They need her to sign a treaty to make this invasion of theirs legal. They can't afford to kill her.
Getting past their blockade is impossible, Your Highness. Any attempt to escape will be dangerous.
We need to free those pilots.
How can you be sure?
The Hutts??
You can't take Her Royal Highness there! The Hutts are gangsters... If they discovered her...
...An extremely well put together little droid. Without a
R2-D2, Your Highness.
Your Highness, Tatooine is very dangerous. It's controlled by an alliance of gangs called the Hutts. I do not agree with the Jedi on this.
Wait!
Her Highness commands you to take her handmaiden
The Queen wishes it. She is curious about this planet.
Don't make me go back and tell her you refuse.
It looks pretty bad. We'd better seal the ship.
Yes?
We'll be right there.
A malfunction?
A communications disruption can only mean one thing. Invasion.
Negotiation? We've lost all communications!...and where ar the the Chancellors Ambassadors? How can we negotiate? We must prepare to defend ourselves.
...how will you explain this invasion to the Senate?
Your negotiations seem to have failed, Ambassador.
They wouldn't dare.
Please, Your Highness, reconsider. Our only hope is for the Senate to side with us... Senator Palpatine will need your help.
Your Highness, I will stay here and do what I can...They will have to retain the Council of Governors in order to maintain control. But you must leave...

...cut off all food supplies until you return...the death toll is catastrophic...we must bow to their wishes, Your Highness...Please tell us what to do! If you can hear us, Your Highness, you must contact me...
Oh, noooooooooo!
Hey, help me! Help me!!
Oyi, mooie-mooie! I luv yous!
I spake.
No...no! Mesa stay...Mesa yous humble servaunt.
Oh boot tis! Tis demunded byda guds. Tis a live debett, tis. Mesa culled Jaja Binkss.
Say what?
Oh, nooooo! Weesa ganna....
...dieeee!
Yousa sav-ed my again, hey?
Mure? Mure did you spake??!?
Ex-squeeze me, but da moto grande safe place would be Otoh Gunga. Tis where I grew up...Tis safe city.
Ahhh, will...on second taut...no, not willy.
Iss embarrissing, boot... My afrai my've bean banished. My forgoten der Bosses would do terrible tings to my. Terrible tings if my goen back dare.
Oh! Yousa point is well seen. Dis way! Hurry!
Wesa goen underwater, okeyday?
My warning yous. Gungans no liken outlaunders. Don't expict a wern welcome.
Heyo-dalee, Cap'n Tarpals, Mesa back!
How wude.
Daza setten yous up. Goen through da planet core is bad bombin!!
Ahhh...any hep hair would be hot.
Oooooh...Ouch!
Count mesa outta dis! Better dead here, den deader in da core...Yee guds, whata mesa sayin?!
Dis is nusen.
Hey, ho? Where wesa goen??
Yo dreamen mesa hopen...
Ooooh, maxibig..."da Force"...Wellen, dat smells stinkowiff.
Tis a long tale, buta small part wawdabe mesa...ooooh...aaaa.....clumsy.
Mesa cause-ed mabee one or duey lettal bitty axadentes...yud-say boom da gasser, un crash Der Bosses heyblibber...den banished.
Oooops.
Wesa free!
What yet? Monstairs out dare! Leak'n in here, all'n sink'n, and nooooo power! You nutsen! WHEN YOUSA TINK WESA IN TROUBLE?!!!?
Monstairs back!
Wesa in trouble now??
Wesa dead yet?? Oie Boie!
Wesa dude it!
Wesa safe now.
Dissen berry good. Hey?
What!!?? Oie boie!
Iyiiyi, wesa die'n here, hey!
No! Too scary!
No a mighty no!
Oie boie...mesa comen. Mesa comen!
Whoa!!!
Yousa guys bombad!
Ello, boyos. Disa wanna longo trip...hey?
Tis opens?...Oooops! Many springs and things come flying out.
Yoi! Just yoken!
Hidoe!
Sorry, nomeanen to scare yousa.
I scovered oily back dare. Needen it?
Mesa Ja Ja Binksss...

Me no know...mesa day starten pitty okeyday witda brisky morning munchen. Den boom....getten berry skeered, un grabbed dat Jedi, and before mesa knowen it...pow! Mesa here. ...getten berry berry skeered.
Obi-Wan, sire, pleeese, no mesa go!
Dis sun doen murder tada skin.
Dissen berry berry bad. Ooooh...icky...icky...goo.
Noah gain...da beings hereabouts cawazy. Wesa be robbed un crunched.
Who, mesa??
Why mesa always da one??
Nosir, nosir. Mesa hate crunchen. Dat's da last ting mesa wanten.
Mesa doen nutten!
Dissen cozy.
How wude.
Wit no-nutten mula to trade.
Wesa ina pitty bad goo.
Who, mesa?
Ouch-dats muy bigo Oucho.
Dis berry loony, Annie. May da guds be kind, mesa palo.
Mesa no watch. Dissen ganna be messy!
Where's Skywalker?
He musta crash-ud.
Noah gain, Jar Jar. Yousa goen tada Bosses. Yousa in big dudu this time.
Yousa cannot bees hair. Dis army of mackineeks up dare tis new weesong!
Wesa no like da Naboo! Un dey no like uss-ens. Da Naboo tink day so smarty den us-ens. Day tink day brains so big.
No, mesa no tink so. Mesa scant talkie witda Naboo, and no nutten talkie it outlaunders. Dos mackineeks no comen here! Dey not know of uss-en.
Wesa wish no nutten in yousa tings, outlaunder, and wesa no care-n about da Naboo.
Wesa gonna speed yousaway.
Wesa give yousa una bongo. Da speedest way tooda Naboo tis goen through da core. Now go.
Binkss brokeen the nocombackie law. Hisen to be pune-ished.
Pounded unto death.
Binks. Yousa havena liveplay with thisen hisen?
Hisen live tis yos, outlauder. Begone wit him.
Good. I have the Senate bogged down in procedures. By the time this incident comes up for a vote, they will have no choice but to accept your control of the system.
Queen Amidala is young and naive. You will find controlling her will not be difficult. You have done well, Viceroy.
Destroy all high-ranking officials, Viceroy...slowly...quietly. And Queen Amidala, has she signed the treaty?
Viceroy, find her! I want that treaty signed.
...not for a Sith...
...Viceroy, this is my apprentice. Lord Maul. He will find your lost ship.
Move against the Jedi first...you will then have no difficulty taking the Queen back to Naboo, where she will sign the treaty.
You have been well trained, my young apprentice, they will be no match for you. It is too late for them to stop us now. Everything is going as planned. The Republic will soon be in my command.
Where are you going?
You're under arrest!
....our communications are still jammed.
Powers back! That little droid did it. He bypassed the main power drive. Deflector shield up, at maximum.
There's not enough power to get us to Coruscant...the hyperdrive is leaking.
There's a settlement...a spaceport, looks like.
Ah yes, ah yes. Nubian. We have lots of that. What kinda junk?

...Here it is...a T-14 hyperdrive generator!! Thee in luck, I'm the only one hereabouts who has one...but thee might as well buy a new ship. It would be cheaper, I think...Sying of which, how's thee going to pay for all this?
Republic credits?!? Republic credits are no good out here. I need something more real...
No they won'ta.

No, they won'ta. What you think you're some kinda Jedi, waving your hand around like that? I'm a Toydarian. Mind tricks don'ta work on me-only money. No money, no parts! No deal! And no one else has a T-14 hyperdrive, I promise you that.
Patta go bolla!
Pedunky. Maa kee cheelya.
The boy tells me you wanta sponser hi insa race. You can't afford parts. How can you do this? Not on Republic credits, I think.
Not bad...not bad...a Nubian.
...but what would the boy ride? He smashed up my Pod in the last race. It will take some time to fix it.
That you did. The boy is good, no doubts there.
I hope you didn't kill anyone I know for it. So, you supply the Pod and the entry fee; I supply the boy. We split the winnings fifty-fifty, I think.
...I want to see your spaceship the moment the race is over.
Not if your ship belongs to me, I think...I warn you, no funny business.
Don't get me wrongo. I have great faith in the boy. He's a credit to your race, but Sebulba there is going to win, I think.
He always wins. I'm betting heavily on Sebulba.
What??!! What do you mean?
A Pod for slaves. I don't think so...well, poerhaps. Just one...the mother, maybe...the boy isn't for sale.
No Pod's worth two slaves...not by a long shot...one slave or nothing.
We'll let fate decide. Blue it's the boy, red his mother...
You won the small toss, outlander, bou you won't win the race, so...it makes little difference.
Are you an angel?

An angel. I've heard the deep space pilots talk about them. They live on the Moons of Iego I think. They are the most beautiful creatures in the universe. They are good and kind, and so pretty they make even the most hardened spice pirate cry.
You must be one...maybe you just don't know it.
Since I was very little, three, I think. My Mom and I were sold to Gardulla the Hutt, but she lost us, betting on the Podraces, to Watto, who's a lot better master than Gardulla, I think.
I am a person! My name is Anakin.
You are a strange girl to me.
Hit the nose!
...wouldn't have lasted long if I weren't so good at fixing things. I'm making my own droid...
...Anakin.
Anakin Skywalker.
I'm glad I met you too.
Because you're afraid.
Hi! Your buddy here was about to be turned into orange goo. He picked a fight with a Dug. An especially dangerous Dug called Sebulba.
Fear attracts the fearful. He was trying to overcome his fear by squashing you...be less afraid.
To a point.
How are you feeling today, Jira?
Guess what? I've found that cooling unit I've been searching for. It's pretty beat up, but I'll have it fixed up for you in no time, I promise.
I'll take four pallies today. You'll like these...
Whoops, I thought I had more...Make that three, I'm not hungry.
Do you have shelter?
Is it far?
You'll never reach the outskirts in time...sandstorms are very, very dangerous. Come with me. Hurry!
Mom! Mom! I'm home.
These are my friends, Mom. This is Padme, and...gee, I don't know any of your names.
I'm building a droid. You wanna see?
A sandstorm, Mom. Listen.
Come on! Let me show you Threepio!
Isn't he great?! He's not finished yet.
You really like him? He's a protocol droid...to help Mom. Watch!
When the storm is over, you can see my racer. I'm building a Podracer!
I've been working on a scanner to try and locate them, but no luck.
...and they blow you up...poof!
Have you ever seen a Podrace?
I'm the only human who can do it.
Mom, what? I'm not bragging. It's true. Watto says he's never heard of a human doing it.
I...I was wondering...something...
Well, ahhh...you're a Jedi Knight, aren't you?
I saw your laser sword. Only Jedi carry that kind of weapon.
I don't think so... No one can kill a Jedi Knight.
I had a dream I was a Jedi. I came back here and freed all the slaves...have you come to free us?
I think you have...why else would you be here?
Coruscant...wow...how did you end up here in the outer rim?
I can help! I can fix anything!
I've built a racer! It's the fastest ever...There's a big race tomorrow, on Boonta Eve. You could enter my pod. It's all but finished...
Watto doesn't know I've built it. You could make him think it's your's, and you could get him to let me pilot it for you.
But Mom, I love it...and they need help...they're in trouble. The prize money would more than pay for the parts they need.
We have to help them, Mom...you said that the biggest problem in the universe is no one helps each other...
Is that a yes? That is a yes!
No batta!
Bayno, Bayno!
Ahhhh....it wasn't my fault really...Sebulba flashed me with his vent ports. I actually saved the Pod...mostly.
Padme and Jar Jar, this is my friend Kitster, and seek, Amee, and Wald.
This isn't the half of it. I'm entered in the Boonta Race tomorrow!
Hey! Jar Jar! Stay away from those energy binders...
If your hand gets caught in that beam, it will go numb for hours.
It will.
Yes, sir!!
There are so many! Do they all have a system of planets?
Has anyone been to them all?
I want to be the first one to see them all... Ouch!
What are you doing?
I've never seen...
You were in my dream...you were leading a huge army into battle.
Hook 'em up, Kitster. I won't be long. Where's Qui-Gon?
What did he mean by that?
Well...not exactly...
...but Kitster's right, I will this time.
I will, Mom. I promise.
I won't let you down.
Hey, that will be seven truguts!!
Bazda wahota, shag. Dobiella Nok. Yoka to Bantha poodoo. 9You won't walk away from this one, slave scum! You're Bantha poodoo.)
The heat's never been kind to me, you know, Annie!
You're a fine boy, Annie.
